1
00:00:25,825 --> 00:00:27,360
What if you were wrong...

2
00:00:28,495 --> 00:00:29,929
and she was right?

3
00:00:34,601 --> 00:00:35,935
What do you mean?

4
00:00:36,870 --> 00:00:40,106
You're wrong. The prosecutor is right.

5
00:00:42,342 --> 00:00:43,376
What?

6
00:00:46,646 --> 00:00:48,848
YEONJU TUNNEL

7
00:01:02,962 --> 00:01:04,264
What do you mean?

8
00:01:05,432 --> 00:01:09,069
I'm wrong and Do-yeon is right?

9
00:01:14,541 --> 00:01:17,877
The twins planned
to kill that man together.

10
00:01:18,611 --> 00:01:19,913
They're co-principals.

11
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:33,426
They're co-principals?

12
00:01:35,695 --> 00:01:37,330
You're lying, right?

13
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:40,834
Tell me it's a lie!

14
00:01:54,647 --> 00:01:56,282
You know I'm not lying.

15
00:01:56,549 --> 00:01:58,818
The twins are both in on this.

16
00:01:59,752 --> 00:02:02,155
I don't know. I can't hear you.

17
00:02:02,689 --> 00:02:05,091
The prosecutor was right
and you were wrong.

18
00:02:05,158 --> 00:02:08,995
So what? The judge already decided
they weren't co-principals.

19
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:13,299
Should I go tell him, "Sorry. I was wrong
and Do-yeon was right"?

20
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,101
No! I can't do that!

21
00:02:17,170 --> 00:02:21,975
Let go! Let go before I get mad.

22
00:02:22,675 --> 00:02:27,480
I'm counting to three. One, two, three...

23
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:30,917
Three...

24
00:02:31,284 --> 00:02:33,920
You should leave the world of law.

25
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:37,157
-What?
-That's what you said ten minutes ago.

26
00:02:38,424 --> 00:02:41,394
Do you know
who should leave the world of law?

27
00:02:42,295 --> 00:02:44,330
A lawyer who always loses?

28
00:02:44,631 --> 00:02:46,633
A judge who always makes wrong judgments?

29
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:50,803
Or a prosecutor
who always makes the wrong indictments?

30
00:02:51,037 --> 00:02:52,238
Shut it.

31
00:02:53,606 --> 00:02:54,774
It's none of the above.

32
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:58,711
The problem is people like you
who won't admit they're wrong.

33
00:03:01,247 --> 00:03:02,916
-But that was--
-Am I wrong?

34
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:10,590
This stalker kid.
I thought he was my hope.

35
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:12,892
But he's just tying me down.

36
00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:29,509
How can he say I'm the same?
We're not even remotely similar!

37
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:32,478
What's wrong with her now?

38
00:04:35,908 --> 00:04:37,010
Anyone home?

39
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:40,446
Yes, who is it?

40
00:04:42,882 --> 00:04:44,217
Do you know this kid?

41
00:04:52,358 --> 00:04:56,329
This kid is tying us down.

42
00:05:13,846 --> 00:05:16,316
I hurt my hand.

43
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,418
What?

44
00:05:19,085 --> 00:05:20,586
I hurt my hand!

45
00:05:21,387 --> 00:05:22,855
It hurts!

46
00:05:48,981 --> 00:05:50,316
Take back what you said.

47
00:05:52,919 --> 00:05:55,655
Take back that I'm just like Do-yeon.

48
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:58,458
No.

49
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:03,830
I'm going to do everything I can
to find the truth.

50
00:06:03,996 --> 00:06:08,134
I'm going to prove
in court the twins are co-principals.

51
00:06:08,301 --> 00:06:10,670
-Do you understand?
-I'm not sure.

52
00:06:12,472 --> 00:06:15,608
I'm going to admit I was wrong, you fool!

53
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:20,747
Are you laughing? Did you just laugh?

54
00:06:21,581 --> 00:06:24,183
Is this funny? Does this look easy?

55
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:26,519
Hey, this is very difficult.

56
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:28,421
Admitting I was wrong,

57
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:31,758
and doing it in front of a foe,
isn't something anyone cannot do.

58
00:06:31,824 --> 00:06:34,026
But I'm going to do it. Why?

59
00:06:34,193 --> 00:06:37,130
Because I'm not just "anyone."

60
00:06:39,132 --> 00:06:40,633
So take back what you said.

61
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:43,136
I'm mistaken from Do-yeon.

62
00:06:44,003 --> 00:06:45,705
It's "different," not "mistaken" from her.

63
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:48,674
-What?
-"Mistaken" means you're not right.

64
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:50,710
"Different" means you're not the same.

65
00:06:51,177 --> 00:06:53,346
So it's "different," not "wrong."

66
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,650
You have such a poor vocabulary.

67
00:06:57,950 --> 00:07:01,587
-I'm not in the mood to--
-You're different from her.

68
00:07:02,822 --> 00:07:04,424
Very different.

69
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,759
-Okay?
-What?

70
00:07:08,728 --> 00:07:09,762
Yes.

71
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:12,865
Okay, then.

72
00:07:13,599 --> 00:07:15,368
Come with me. We have a lot to buy.

73
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:19,172
Why do I have to come?

74
00:07:30,049 --> 00:07:32,985
It would take too long to wash
and chop these all up.

75
00:07:33,586 --> 00:07:36,456
I would have to spend 30 minutes,
on what could take 3 minutes...

76
00:07:55,675 --> 00:07:57,310
YEONJU DETENTION CENTER

77
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:01,214
What should we do now?

78
00:08:01,514 --> 00:08:04,217
Do we have to gather more evidence
that I didn't do it?

79
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:08,354
Or should I get petitions from my friends?

80
00:08:08,688 --> 00:08:09,889
Before that happens,

81
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:17,363
are you sure you didn't lie,
not even one percent?

82
00:08:19,365 --> 00:08:20,466
I didn't.

83
00:08:20,533 --> 00:08:26,973
A one-percent lie could make
the other ninety-nine percent a lie, too.

84
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:32,044
I know. Why are you asking?

85
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:35,047
I'm asking just to be sure.

86
00:08:35,615 --> 00:08:40,820
Did you and your brother plan
to kill Ham Ki-su together?

87
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:42,255
No, absolutely not!

88
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,792
Why? Did my brother say something?

89
00:08:48,761 --> 00:08:50,997
If your brother says something,

90
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:56,969
then will the fact that you both planned
to kill him be revealed?

91
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:17,290
That's not what I mean.

92
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:21,260
But in case you did hear something...

93
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:28,000
It's a secret.

94
00:09:29,201 --> 00:09:31,070
A lawyer shouldn't talk about it.

95
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:33,839
Attorney Code of Conduct, Article 23.

96
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:37,643
"An attorney may not reveal
confidential communications

97
00:09:38,544 --> 00:09:40,046
of the client learned
during one's employ."

98
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:42,481
You know that, right?

99
00:09:43,349 --> 00:09:45,084
Are you threatening me?

100
00:09:48,921 --> 00:09:49,956
No.

101
00:09:50,957 --> 00:09:55,261
I just wanted you to know
that I'm smarter than I look.

102
00:09:58,331 --> 00:10:03,035
So you just have to trust me
and do as I say.

103
00:10:03,202 --> 00:10:05,471
Just as you have until now.

104
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:10,076
I studied some law.

105
00:10:11,944 --> 00:10:16,415
The law is not something to abide by,
but to use well.

106
00:10:25,758 --> 00:10:28,694
What a jerk. How do I get him?

107
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:32,765
Shall I just say everything,
despite attorney-client privilege?

108
00:10:32,932 --> 00:10:36,602
No, I'm an attorney.
It's how I make a living.

109
00:10:37,403 --> 00:10:38,638
Damn it.

110
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:44,810
-Ms. Jjang.
-Mr. Cha.

111
00:10:44,877 --> 00:10:48,114
-I'm glad we met. Let's talk.
-But I have to go to court!

112
00:10:49,849 --> 00:10:52,451
I just met with Jeong Pil-seung.

113
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:56,722
We can't talk about that.
I'm Jeong Pil-jae's attorney.

114
00:10:57,189 --> 00:10:59,992
-You have to hear this. The two of them--
-I can't hear you.

115
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:02,962
-Hear me out!
-I can't hear you.

116
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:04,630
I think they planned it.

117
00:11:05,131 --> 00:11:06,499
Don't hang onto me...

118
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:08,768
They're exploiting the fact
they're twins to get out of this.

119
00:11:08,834 --> 00:11:10,803
We're both being used by them!

120
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:11,871
Stop it.

121
00:11:12,838 --> 00:11:15,341
I'm sorry, but I won't listen to you.

122
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:17,743
I'm only going to listen
to my client, Jeong Pil-jae.

123
00:11:24,617 --> 00:11:28,454
What a fool. I'm surrounded by fools.

124
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,260
What if it's true?

125
00:11:35,394 --> 00:11:37,029
"They planned it"?

126
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:41,934
Get a hold of yourself!
You're Jeong Pil-jae's attorney.

127
00:11:42,635 --> 00:11:45,137
I have to fight Ms. Jjang.
She's the enemy.

128
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,872
Let's not be affected!

129
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:50,109
What?

130
00:11:55,181 --> 00:11:56,248
What's wrong?

131
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:01,654
It's Ms. Jjang.

132
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:06,926
I have never seen such a fool like him.

133
00:12:07,126 --> 00:12:10,629
He covered his ears and shouted like this.

134
00:12:10,796 --> 00:12:12,264
What's wrong with him?

135
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:14,767
He did look a little uptight.

136
00:12:16,702 --> 00:12:18,604
Right? You agree, right?

137
00:12:18,771 --> 00:12:20,106
What are you doing about the trial?

138
00:12:22,775 --> 00:12:23,976
I don't know.

139
00:12:24,977 --> 00:12:28,881
All the evidence is weak.
There's nothing concrete.

140
00:12:29,115 --> 00:12:32,218
With this,
both of them could be found not guilty.

141
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:34,987
How could Do-yeon indict
with this evidence?

142
00:12:35,054 --> 00:12:36,255
There's one thing.

143
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:38,424
What is it?

144
00:12:38,491 --> 00:12:41,727
I read the prosecutor's mind
when you two were talking.

145
00:12:42,361 --> 00:12:44,697
What did she say?
She talked bad about me, right?

146
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:48,367
-No. She asked for help.
-What?

147
00:12:50,402 --> 00:12:54,573
You do?
Both of them could be found innocent.

148
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:59,211
But if I didn't do anything,
both of them could have gone to prison.

149
00:13:00,079 --> 00:13:05,384
Shall I ask for help?
With her, I could get both of them.

150
00:13:07,319 --> 00:13:08,654
What was her plan?

151
00:13:08,721 --> 00:13:11,056
I don't know. I couldn't read that far.

152
00:13:11,757 --> 00:13:14,126
Shall I help her?

153
00:13:15,494 --> 00:13:19,331
Forget it. But maybe I should meet her.

154
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,201
Do-yeon did say
that she had something crucial.

155
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:26,005
Are you crazy? Rely on Seo Do-yeon? No.

156
00:13:30,543 --> 00:13:32,178
What are you doing with my cell phone?

157
00:13:32,845 --> 00:13:34,146
I'm texting Seo Do-yeon.

158
00:13:34,313 --> 00:13:38,184
What? Are you crazy? Text her?
Give it to me. Hey!

159
00:13:38,684 --> 00:13:40,986
I'm almost done.

160
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:44,356
Give it back to me. Hey!

161
00:13:56,969 --> 00:13:58,671
Did you really send this?

162
00:13:59,638 --> 00:14:00,673
Yes.

163
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:06,278
JANG HYE-SEONG

164
00:14:06,445 --> 00:14:10,983
Can we meet tomorrow?
I think it would be a win-win.

165
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:18,390
TO: YEONJU DISTRICT COURT
REQUEST FOR CHANGE OF INDICTMENT

166
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:28,234
With her, it's not a win-win,
but a lose-lose situation.

167
00:14:29,735 --> 00:14:34,773
Oh no. I seem like a loser.
Not just a loser, but a pathetic one!

168
00:14:37,476 --> 00:14:40,279
At the crime scene. 7:30 a.m.

169
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:43,449
"7:30 a.m."?

170
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:46,518
Who told her to set the time and place?
I'm not going.

171
00:14:49,154 --> 00:14:52,725
You said you would admit you're wrong.
Go tell her and hear her out.

172
00:14:52,992 --> 00:14:56,195
My gosh.
I want to zip up that mouth of yours.

173
00:15:04,370 --> 00:15:07,506
The victim had three kids in total.

174
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:11,744
The first one started school this year,
and the second is autistic.

175
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:14,947
The third child just turned one.

176
00:15:15,447 --> 00:15:19,051
The father was murdered
the day before his first birthday.

177
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:21,420
Why did you want to meet me here?

178
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:24,823
Do you want me to feel guilty
by seeing the victim's family?

179
00:15:25,691 --> 00:15:27,226
You said your defendant is innocent.

180
00:15:28,027 --> 00:15:30,129
Why would you feel guilty?

181
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:36,568
You found out they're co-principals,
right?

182
00:15:38,203 --> 00:15:41,807
No comment. You're the prosecutor,
and I'm the public defender.

183
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,045
I'm sticking to the indictment.

184
00:15:46,845 --> 00:15:48,914
I'm not being stubborn or persistent.

185
00:15:49,715 --> 00:15:51,951
I'm sure that they're co-principals.

186
00:15:53,385 --> 00:15:55,988
Then you should offer hard evidence,
not just hunches.

187
00:15:56,155 --> 00:15:57,990
All your evidence is weak.

188
00:15:58,590 --> 00:16:01,593
I might not have the evidence,
but I have a plan to get them.

189
00:16:03,996 --> 00:16:05,230
What kind of "plan"?

190
00:16:06,231 --> 00:16:08,634
If I tell you, will you help?

191
00:16:10,235 --> 00:16:12,705
Shall I tell you or not?

192
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,976
If you do, do it right.

193
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:21,313
Don't beat around the bush
as you did before.

194
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:25,918
Here's my strategy.

195
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:40,165
Why are they together?

196
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:44,003
Ms. Jang was meeting with Ms. Seo?

197
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:45,704
At the crime scene?

198
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:51,210
What would a prosecutor
and public defender have to talk about?

199
00:16:51,477 --> 00:16:57,049
Do you think they're going
to work together to attack you?

200
00:16:57,116 --> 00:17:01,553
That would be so wrong.
How could an attorney do that?

201
00:17:01,653 --> 00:17:04,423
Ms. Jang could do that. Don't you agree?

202
00:17:05,424 --> 00:17:06,525
Mr. Cha.

203
00:17:07,559 --> 00:17:10,896
I was really moved.

204
00:17:11,897 --> 00:17:12,731
By what?

205
00:17:12,798 --> 00:17:14,333
It was 7:30 a.m.

206
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,836
That shows how passionate
she is about this case.

207
00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:21,940
I know I would do it,
but I didn't expect her to.

208
00:17:22,674 --> 00:17:24,810
Don't you think she's quite devoted?

209
00:17:25,077 --> 00:17:29,314
"Devoted"? How can your conclusion be
that she's "devoted"?

210
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:30,949
What else could there be?

211
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:36,088
He's so positive. Way too positive.

212
00:17:37,289 --> 00:17:38,223
Sweet.

213
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:42,094
NOT GUILTY PLEA SUMMARY
GUILTY PLEA SUMMARY

214
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:44,096
Choose.

215
00:17:44,663 --> 00:17:46,331
This is for confessing to the crime...

216
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,601
And this is for not confessing
to the crime.

217
00:17:50,536 --> 00:17:52,104
Of course I won't confess.

218
00:17:53,672 --> 00:17:57,042
Even if you could be found not guilty
if you confessed?

219
00:18:00,813 --> 00:18:02,781
What are you trying to trick me into?

220
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,552
Let me explain.

221
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:10,656
First, the plan is
to make all evidence inadmissible.

222
00:18:10,889 --> 00:18:15,694
Not just yours,
but even Jeong Pil-jae's evidence, too.

223
00:18:15,961 --> 00:18:18,397
Not just mine, but my brother's, too?

224
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:19,765
Yes.

225
00:18:19,832 --> 00:18:21,300
Once all the evidence

226
00:18:21,366 --> 00:18:24,603
that you two had committed homicide
by robbery is dismissed,

227
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:28,073
then you're going to confess.

228
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:32,444
Are you kidding?
How can I be found innocent then?

229
00:18:32,845 --> 00:18:35,314
Article 310
of the Criminal Procedure Code.

230
00:18:35,447 --> 00:18:37,616
"The corroboration of a confession.

231
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:41,420
When the defendant's
confession is the only evidence,

232
00:18:41,487 --> 00:18:44,056
that defendant cannot be found guilty."

233
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:49,228
Even if you confess, there is no
other evidence, so you're innocent.

234
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:54,166
But your brother, who did not confess,
will be found guilty.

235
00:18:54,766 --> 00:18:55,767
What?

236
00:18:56,568 --> 00:18:59,905
There's no evidence against him either,
so how will he be found guilty?

237
00:19:00,839 --> 00:19:03,742
There is evidence. It's you.

238
00:19:04,176 --> 00:19:08,180
Your confession will be
corroborating evidence for him.

239
00:19:08,614 --> 00:19:14,520
So even if he denies it,
your confession will become new evidence.

240
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,890
In this case,
your brother will be found guilty.

241
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:19,525
Isn't it amazing?

242
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:23,495
Innocent if you confess
and guilty if you don't.

243
00:19:23,595 --> 00:19:25,531
Why should I confess
if there is no evidence?

244
00:19:25,731 --> 00:19:28,133
If I don't confess,
we'll both be found innocent.

245
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:32,204
What if the prosecutor
is holding back evidence on purpose?

246
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:35,707
-What do you mean?
-I looked at the evidence list.

247
00:19:36,041 --> 00:19:38,410
She submitted
only one of the security videos.

248
00:19:38,644 --> 00:19:40,112
There are actually two.

249
00:19:40,812 --> 00:19:45,350
And she purposefully submitted the footage
that wasn't as clear.

250
00:19:45,551 --> 00:19:46,919
What could that mean?

251
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:51,623
I think the prosecutor
has set up this situation.

252
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:55,594
She's opening the door,
