Why aren't you answering that?

499
00:37:25,209 --> 00:37:26,944
RECORD

500
00:37:30,214 --> 00:37:31,249
Hello?

501
00:37:31,582 --> 00:37:32,883
It's been a long time, Su-ha.

502
00:37:33,684 --> 00:37:34,785
How have you been?

503
00:37:36,153 --> 00:37:37,054
Who is it?

504
00:37:37,722 --> 00:37:40,124
Why don't you reply? Are you listening?

505
00:37:41,692 --> 00:37:42,727
Keep talking.

506
00:37:58,776 --> 00:37:59,877
What is it now?

507
00:38:00,244 --> 00:38:01,779
Min Jun-guk called me.

508
00:38:02,580 --> 00:38:04,615
He did? Why all of a sudden?

509
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:10,421
-You heard I had moved, right?
-Where are you?

510
00:38:10,855 --> 00:38:15,226
-Where are you right now?
-Forget about me and live your life.

511
00:38:16,027 --> 00:38:19,196
I won't forget either of you
and will live my life to the fullest.

512
00:38:19,764 --> 00:38:21,365
I called to tell you that.

513
00:38:21,932 --> 00:38:23,467
This is a threat, isn't it?

514
00:38:24,568 --> 00:38:26,103
Think what you want.

515
00:38:27,171 --> 00:38:29,640
So what? He just called to say hi.

516
00:38:30,608 --> 00:38:33,210
Does it sound like that to you?
He said he wouldn't forget us.

517
00:38:33,277 --> 00:38:34,912
Of course he shouldn't.

518
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:38,149
With an atoning heart, he said he would
live his life to the best and not forget.

519
00:38:39,183 --> 00:38:41,118
It sounds like a threat to me.

520
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:46,524
Where did he move to?
You must know where he is.

521
00:38:46,590 --> 00:38:48,559
What? Well...

522
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:51,962
We should've asked where he was going.

523
00:38:54,965 --> 00:38:56,300
You really don't know?

524
00:38:56,901 --> 00:38:59,904
Why do you want to know?
So you can beat him up again?

525
00:39:05,042 --> 00:39:09,046
If you don't do anything,
I might go and kill him.

526
00:39:09,413 --> 00:39:10,414
What?

527
00:39:11,549 --> 00:39:14,885
Su-ha, I'll be keeping an eye on you.
I've warned you!

528
00:39:24,962 --> 00:39:26,564
Where is Mr. Cha?

529
00:39:26,897 --> 00:39:30,468
He went early to meet the twin client.
He should be back soon.

530
00:39:31,202 --> 00:39:33,204
It's already past noon.

531
00:39:33,704 --> 00:39:37,041
-Shall we all go eat?
-Let's wait for Mr. Cha.

532
00:39:38,342 --> 00:39:42,346
I have plans with a friend,
so please excuse me.

533
00:39:42,513 --> 00:39:46,283
"A friend"? Do you have any friends?

534
00:39:46,884 --> 00:39:51,756
Mr. Shin, why are you suddenly so cold
to Ms. Jang?

535
00:39:53,691 --> 00:39:58,696
To me, Ms. Jjang is not a lawyer.

536
00:40:03,634 --> 00:40:06,504
Ms. Jang, you said you have plans, right?

537
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:08,205
Yes, I do.

538
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:10,741
And I have a lot of friends.

539
00:40:11,208 --> 00:40:14,979
I have friends lined up
to have lunch with me.

540
00:40:28,292 --> 00:40:30,327
Can I have some more kimchi, please?

541
00:40:35,332 --> 00:40:37,168
Why did they have to come here?

542
00:40:41,539 --> 00:40:43,607
Three beef bone broth soups, please.

543
00:40:44,542 --> 00:40:45,843
Why didn't Ms. Jjang come out?

544
00:40:46,010 --> 00:40:48,946
She left, saying she has plans
with a friend.

545
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:51,649
She's probably eating alone somewhere.

546
00:40:52,750 --> 00:40:54,885
How was your meeting with the twin client?

547
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:56,454
Did he tell you why they killed him?

548
00:40:57,588 --> 00:41:00,124
Yes. It was revenge.

549
00:41:01,525 --> 00:41:05,930
The mart owner raped
the younger twin's girlfriend.

550
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:10,167
And he even threatened to send photos
of it to her workplace if she reported it.

551
00:41:11,101 --> 00:41:14,572
That's why the boyfriend planned
and killed the man with his brother.

552
00:41:15,573 --> 00:41:18,142
There's robbery, murder, conspiracy,
and lack of remorse.

553
00:41:18,242 --> 00:41:21,645
He denied the charges
and caused a scene in court.

554
00:41:22,346 --> 00:41:24,315
He's probably getting a heavy sentence.

555
00:41:25,683 --> 00:41:29,687
If I were his counsel,
I would've persuaded him to confess.

556
00:41:30,454 --> 00:41:32,523
I would've made him admit it
and show remorse,

557
00:41:32,723 --> 00:41:34,825
and gotten the sentence reduced
by three or four years.

558
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:39,463
I'm not being cocky.
That's what a lawyer should do.

559
00:41:40,764 --> 00:41:44,168
I'm sorry. This trial is already over.

560
00:41:44,668 --> 00:41:49,006
But I hope they meet someone like you
in the court of appeals.

561
00:41:50,207 --> 00:41:54,745
Is it true that Ms. Jang worked
with the prosecutor on this?

562
00:41:54,845 --> 00:41:56,146
To prove them guilty?

563
00:41:57,548 --> 00:41:59,650
You knew, right?

564
00:42:00,284 --> 00:42:02,853
A surveillance video was missing
from the evidence list.

565
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:05,523
So I knew what was going on
in a general sense.

566
00:42:06,590 --> 00:42:11,428
Aren't you mad?
She did what a lawyer shouldn't do.

567
00:42:13,430 --> 00:42:16,767
She revealed the truth in her own way.

568
00:42:19,970 --> 00:42:22,706
I think Ms. Jjang is wrong.

569
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:27,177
I don't think she's wrong.

570
00:42:29,179 --> 00:42:31,048
I just think she's different from me.

571
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:35,853
You're positive. Way too positive.

572
00:42:36,287 --> 00:42:37,988
Here's your kimchi.

573
00:42:38,722 --> 00:42:41,025
What are you doing down there?

574
00:42:49,166 --> 00:42:52,169
Ms. Jang? You were here?

575
00:42:53,037 --> 00:42:54,038
Yes.

576
00:42:55,606 --> 00:42:57,908
There was some money on the floor.

577
00:42:58,075 --> 00:43:00,578
What happened to your friend?
Why are you alone?

578
00:43:02,646 --> 00:43:04,114
She left first.

579
00:43:05,849 --> 00:43:07,251
How much is this?

580
00:43:10,888 --> 00:43:14,091
Do you think she heard what we said?

581
00:43:14,224 --> 00:43:15,359
Whatever.

582
00:43:21,565 --> 00:43:22,766
Did you hear everything?

583
00:43:24,335 --> 00:43:27,071
I don't feel sorry to you at all.

584
00:43:27,137 --> 00:43:29,073
And I don't think I was wrong.

585
00:43:29,139 --> 00:43:31,775
I know. I don't think so either.

586
00:43:33,944 --> 00:43:34,979
Okay then.

587
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:40,684
What are you doing tonight?

588
00:43:41,185 --> 00:43:43,754
-What?
-There's a movie I want to watch.

589
00:43:44,855 --> 00:43:47,558
-Is this--
-It's not a date.

590
00:43:47,758 --> 00:43:50,427
I just can't go to the movies alone.

591
00:43:50,527 --> 00:43:52,796
So I go to the movies
with just about anyone.

592
00:43:52,963 --> 00:43:55,099
It's not a date,
so don't take it the wrong way.

593
00:43:55,265 --> 00:43:56,266
Okay.

594
00:43:56,767 --> 00:44:00,404
Then... See you later at Phillip Cinema
at 6:30 p.m.

595
00:44:00,471 --> 00:44:01,372
Okay.

596
00:44:01,438 --> 00:44:06,210
And glasses, parted hair, and white socks
with black shoes are prohibited.

597
00:44:06,276 --> 00:44:07,244
Okay...

598
00:44:08,912 --> 00:44:10,280
This is my style.

599
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:13,984
Understood.

600
00:44:14,184 --> 00:44:19,289
Four thousand won!
A talking doll for four thousand won.

601
00:44:19,356 --> 00:44:20,891
LET YOUR LOVERS
AND FRIENDS HEAR YOUR VOICE

602
00:44:22,793 --> 00:44:24,428
How do you record this?

603
00:44:24,762 --> 00:44:27,731
To record, press the foot.

604
00:44:27,798 --> 00:44:30,834
You can record, "I love you, I love you."

605
00:44:30,901 --> 00:44:34,538
And when you press the belly,
the recording plays. Test for yourself.

606
00:44:44,648 --> 00:44:45,582
How much is this?

607
00:44:50,254 --> 00:44:51,588
Get that man!

608
00:44:54,992 --> 00:44:56,226
Stop right there!

609
00:44:58,429 --> 00:44:59,697
Hey, you!

610
00:45:03,967 --> 00:45:05,002
Get out of the way!

611
00:45:06,136 --> 00:45:08,005
Come on, buddy, drop the knife!

612
00:45:25,556 --> 00:45:27,458
Let me go!

613
00:45:28,492 --> 00:45:30,728
Let go!

614
00:45:33,964 --> 00:45:38,168
Hey! Go over there.
We'll take care of this.

615
00:45:44,775 --> 00:45:46,910
I think I would do a better job than you.

616
00:45:51,648 --> 00:45:52,649
Let go!

617
00:45:59,156 --> 00:46:00,390
Don't move!

618
00:46:07,030 --> 00:46:10,267
-Let go!
-Thank you so much, Su-ha.

619
00:46:10,934 --> 00:46:14,071
We'll make sure
to give you a commendation.

620
00:46:14,138 --> 00:46:16,406
-I don't need one.
-Gosh.

621
00:46:16,707 --> 00:46:21,411
Don't worry about Min Jun-guk.
We're keeping an eye on him.

622
00:46:22,312 --> 00:46:25,315
Lies. I can't believe in you all anymore.

623
00:46:45,903 --> 00:46:46,904
Where are you going?

624
00:46:48,472 --> 00:46:49,606
Well...

625
00:46:50,340 --> 00:46:53,744
He'll scoff if I say I have a date
with Mr. Cha.

626
00:46:54,545 --> 00:46:55,746
A date with Mr. Cha?

627
00:46:57,214 --> 00:46:59,550
It's not a date.

628
00:46:59,883 --> 00:47:02,953
I'm just taking him
to the movies as a reward.

629
00:47:03,353 --> 00:47:04,588
A "reward"?

630
00:47:07,257 --> 00:47:10,527
You know I betrayed Mr. Cha
in the trial, right?

631
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:13,430
I thought he would be mad
but he acknowledged me instead.

632
00:47:13,764 --> 00:47:15,265
He saw what I did.

633
00:47:15,666 --> 00:47:18,335
So I'm accompanying him
to a movie as a reward.

634
00:47:19,603 --> 00:47:22,005
Mr. Cha said what I really wanted to hear.

635
00:47:22,306 --> 00:47:25,108
He said I wasn't wrong
and that I did the right thing.

636
00:47:27,077 --> 00:47:28,078
Did he?

637
00:47:31,315 --> 00:47:32,482
I'm going to be late.

638
00:47:32,549 --> 00:47:36,453
There's food in the fridge
that my mother sent, so eat that.

639
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:37,721
Okay.

640
00:47:55,038 --> 00:47:57,107
Ms. Jjang. Good job.

641
00:48:01,378 --> 00:48:03,647
Ms. Jjang. Good job.

642
00:48:04,581 --> 00:48:06,917
Ms. Jjang. Good job.

643
00:48:28,438 --> 00:48:31,341
I took off my glasses and styled my hair.

644
00:48:32,476 --> 00:48:33,610
And I'm wearing black socks.

645
00:48:34,845 --> 00:48:36,046
Everything is perfect.

646
00:48:36,847 --> 00:48:38,482
Ms. Jjang. Hello...

647
00:48:41,852 --> 00:48:44,688
Ms. Jjang. Hi.

648
00:48:52,296 --> 00:48:54,564
AN EXCITING FIRST DATE IS
INCOMPLETE WITHOUT ROYCE CHOCOLATE

649
00:49:03,106 --> 00:49:06,443
-How much time before your date?
-Why?

650
00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:11,515
Our chocolate is more delicious when cold,
so we pack it with ice.

651
00:49:12,215 --> 00:49:15,152
It won't be that long. About 20 minutes?

652
00:49:15,218 --> 00:49:17,621
Then I'll put enough in for an hour.

653
00:49:17,688 --> 00:49:18,822
Thank you.

654
00:49:20,857 --> 00:49:22,759
Look at the weather.

655
00:49:26,330 --> 00:49:31,435
What have you been doing since before?
Did you drop some money on the floor?

656
00:49:32,903 --> 00:49:36,840
I'm in trouble. I think I lost my gun.

657
00:49:36,907 --> 00:49:38,709
-What?
-Be quiet.

658
00:49:39,609 --> 00:49:42,379
-When?
-I'm not sure.

659
00:49:48,919 --> 00:49:53,056
Hey! Go over there.
We'll take care of this.

660
00:49:57,260 --> 00:50:01,365
If you don't do anything,
I might go and kill him.

661
00:50:02,165 --> 00:50:03,867
Could he have taken it?

662
00:50:19,249 --> 00:50:23,286
No, that is too sexy for Mr. Cha.

663
00:50:30,260 --> 00:50:31,428
Ms. Jjang!

664
00:50:37,567 --> 00:50:41,071
With his hair like that,
Mr. Cha is not too bad to look at.

665
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:48,445
Shall I give him something to see, too?

666
00:50:53,417 --> 00:50:54,551
Hello?

667
00:50:54,751 --> 00:50:57,954
Ms. Jang? Are you with Su-ha?

668
00:50:58,422 --> 00:51:00,590
No. Why?

669
00:51:00,757 --> 00:51:02,993
I think I lost my gun.

670
00:51:04,261 --> 00:51:05,328
And?

671
00:51:05,395 --> 00:51:07,564
I think Su-ha stole it.

672
00:51:07,998 --> 00:51:08,832
What?

673
00:51:09,332 --> 00:51:11,802
He said he would find Min Jun-guk
and kill him.

674
00:51:12,769 --> 00:51:15,539
Where is he right now? Is he at home?

675
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:26,883
Taxi!

676
00:51:29,820 --> 00:51:33,156
Ms. Jjang! Where are you going? Ms. Jjang!

677
00:51:46,703 --> 00:51:48,472
Answer your phone, come on.

678
00:51:53,610 --> 00:51:55,545
JJANG OF ARC

679
00:52:15,665 --> 00:52:17,300
Su-ha! Park Su-ha!

680
00:52:22,372 --> 00:52:24,107
Why are you here? What about your date?

681
00:52:24,241 --> 00:52:25,542
Did you, by any chance...

682
00:52:26,109 --> 00:52:28,411
Ms. Jang!

683
00:52:28,545 --> 00:52:31,081
-Are you inside?
-Yes, one moment!

684
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:35,152
-They're already here to catch him.
-What do you mean, "catch" me?

685
00:52:38,755 --> 00:52:39,789
Ms. Jang.

686
00:52:42,692 --> 00:52:45,595
Don't move from here.
And don't make a sound.

687
00:52:51,801 --> 00:52:54,804
Ms. Jang, I'm the detective
who called you just now.

688
00:52:55,438 --> 00:52:57,073
Hold on. I'll be right out.

689
00:52:59,943 --> 00:53:04,648
Sorry it took so long.
I'm sorry, I was washing my hair.

690
00:53:04,714 --> 00:53:06,016
So you can't come in.

691
00:53:06,383 --> 00:53:10,353
Su-ha isn't at home.
But I keep an eye on him every day.

692
00:53:10,487 --> 00:53:12,455
He won't do anything bad,
so you don't have to worry.

693
00:53:12,689 --> 00:53:15,825
That's not it. I just found the gun.

694
00:53:16,092 --> 00:53:18,061
It was under the seat of the police car.

695
00:53:18,895 --> 00:53:20,497
I came to tell you that.

696
00:53:23,333 --> 00:53:26,069
-What a relief.
-Are you okay?

697
00:53:27,470 --> 00:53:29,506
No, I'm not okay!

698
00:53:30,407 --> 00:53:31,741
Ms. Jang?

699
00:53:31,808 --> 00:53:34,110
How could you scare me like that?

700
00:53:34,177 --> 00:53:36,346
Do you know what I was thinking
while I ran back home?

701
00:53:36,613 --> 00:53:38,548
You said you were washing your hair.

702
00:53:38,615 --> 00:53:42,252
I meant, do you know what I was thinking
while I washed my hair?

703
00:53:43,520 --> 00:53:46,489
Su-ha isn't someone
who would do such a thing.

704
00:53:46,723 --> 00:53:48,558
He would never do anything like that.

705
00:53:49,693 --> 00:53:51,962
I was so offended and worried as well.

706
00:53:52,128 --> 00:53:54,731
Don't you ever make
such unfounded accusations again.

707
00:53:54,798 --> 00:53:55,732
I'm sorry.

708
00:54:17,554 --> 00:54:18,722
Did you hear everything?

709
00:54:20,824 --> 00:54:22,926
Did you think I could have stolen the gun?

710
00:54:25,161 --> 00:54:26,096
Yes.

711
00:54:27,964 --> 00:54:31,668
Is he mad that I suspected him?
What is he thinking?

712
00:54:32,035 --> 00:54:33,370
Nothing much.

713
00:54:34,271 --> 00:54:38,408
I'm thinking you must be embarrassed
about how you look.

714
00:54:39,709 --> 00:54:42,512
No, I'm not embarrassed.

715
00:54:47,250 --> 00:54:52,522
And I thought, "I have someone
who worries about me now."

716
00:55:06,836 --> 00:55:07,937
Who are you?

717
00:55:14,744 --> 00:55:15,945
CHA GUAN-WOO

718
00:55:16,379 --> 00:55:17,647
Oh no!

719
00:55:20,216 --> 00:55:21,184
Hello?

720
00:55:21,451 --> 00:55:23,820
It's me. What happened?

721
00:55:25,355 --> 00:55:27,724
Oh, hi. It was nothing.

722
00:55:28,124 --> 00:55:31,094
I thought a friend had gotten
into trouble, so I rushed over.

723
00:55:31,494 --> 00:55:34,197
-But it's been solved.
-That's a relief.

724
00:55:34,531 --> 00:55:37,667
You didn't answer your phone,
so I thought something happened.

725
00:55:38,068 --> 00:55:40,870
I'm sorry. I was distracted.

726
00:55:41,304 --> 00:55:43,940
-Did you get home okay?
-What?

727
00:55:45,175 --> 00:55:49,112
Yes, of course. I just got home.

728
00:55:49,546 --> 00:55:53,149
I'm really sorry.
We'll see a movie next time.

729
00:55:54,651 --> 00:55:58,088
Okay. See you tomorrow at the office.

730
00:56:11,768 --> 00:56:15,271
It must have all melted.
I should have asked for three hours.

731
00:56:24,581 --> 00:56:25,849
Isn't that...

732
00:56:27,550 --> 00:56:29,586
I'll take Ms. Jang home.

733
00:56:36,626 --> 00:56:37,627
What?

734
00:56:41,297 --> 00:56:42,532
What are you looking at?

735
00:56:44,634 --> 00:56:45,635
Is something there?

736
00:56:51,374 --> 00:56:53,610
I'll bring the laundry in. Go on in.

737
00:56:54,077 --> 00:56:55,779
-Really?
-Yes.

738
00:57:15,432 --> 00:57:19,469
-Did you talk to Mr. Cha?
-Yes, he's already at his place.

739
00:57:21,237 --> 00:57:22,071
Really?

740
00:57:22,138 --> 00:57:25,375
I thought you were empty-headed,
but you're not.

741
00:57:25,842 --> 00:57:27,510
You have better grades than expected.

742
00:57:27,644 --> 00:57:28,578
REPORT CARD

743
00:57:28,678 --> 00:57:30,547
You're in the top tier.

744
00:57:30,814 --> 00:57:33,149
What? Did you go through my bag?

745
00:57:33,583 --> 00:57:37,220
Do you cheat when you take tests?

746
00:57:37,387 --> 00:57:39,589
Do you look into the teacher's minds?

747
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:46,830
They have to be thinking
about the questions for that to work.

748
00:57:47,096 --> 00:57:48,231
It's not like that.

749
00:57:48,498 --> 00:57:50,567
So you were born smart?

750
00:57:51,501 --> 00:57:56,206
I just tend to understand things better
than others in class.

751
00:57:56,906 --> 00:57:59,876
I can read the teachers' minds,
so it works automatically.

752
00:58:02,011 --> 00:58:03,847
Actually, I'm quite offended.

753
00:58:04,647 --> 00:58:06,282
I'm smarter than I look?

754
00:58:07,016 --> 00:58:08,318
How do I look to you?

755
00:58:08,384 --> 00:58:10,553
You look like a total punk.

756
00:58:10,954 --> 00:58:12,889
And when you frown, you're quite scary.

757
00:58:12,989 --> 00:58:16,693
So I guess you thought
I could have stolen the gun.

758
00:58:18,495 --> 00:58:20,864
Were you so scared
that you canceled your date?

759
00:58:21,931 --> 00:58:25,468
I wasn't scared. I was worried.

760
00:58:26,503 --> 00:58:30,640
